item.title: Telefonica Deutschland Earnings Fall Short
item.description: Telefonica Deutschland reported below-forecast adjusted earnings in the first quarter and said it continued to expect low single-digit percentage year-on-year growth for revenue and Oibda.

item.title: Little Relative Value Seen in Germany's August 2053 Bund Pre-Auction
item.description: Germany’s 1.80% August 2053 Bund, one of the two ultra-long bonds to be auctioned on Wednesday, offers limited relative value both on the domestic curve and on cross-market basis, Citi said.

item.title: Spot Gold May Rise Further Toward $2,100/oz
item.description: Spot gold may rise further toward the top of an ascending and broadening wedge, which is now near $2,100/oz, based on the daily chart, said UOB.

item.title: Sterling Could Rise if BOE Signals Further Rate Increases
item.description: Sterling could rise as the BOE is likely to raise interest rates by 25bp to 4.5% as expected on Thursday and potentially signal further increases, Ebury said.

item.title: Alstom Meets Hopes as Orders Jump
item.description: Alstom posted an 11% rise in full-year earnings as sales and orders grew and for fiscal 2024, targeted an adjusted EBIT margin of around 6% and “significantly positive” free cash flow.

item.title: Ahold Delhaize Outperforms Thanks to a Strong U.S.
item.description: Ahold Delhaize posted a slightly higher first-quarter net profit of €561 million, helped by a strong performance in the U.S., with net sales excluding gas rising 6.2%.

item.title: TUI Losses Narrow; Summer Bookings Rebound
item.description: TUI reported a narrower underlying EBIT loss of EUR242 million for the second quarter as revenue improved, and said it expected summer bookings to be at 96% of prepandemic levels.

item.title: Airbus Still Facing Supply-Chain Issues
item.description: Airbus won’t be a short-term pick for Berenberg until a clear improvement in the supply-chain situation helps take the risk out of 24-month forward estimates.

item.title: Credit Agricole Beats Hopes Despite Amundi Outflows
item.description: Credit Agricole reported first-quarter net profit and revenue that came in above expectations despite net outflows of €9.7 billion at its asset management division.

item.title: Toyota Motor's Net Profit Rose on Sales Recovery, Weaker Yen
item.description: Toyota Motor’s fourth-quarter net profit rose 3.4%, thanks in part to a recovery in sales and a weaker yen.

item.title: Siemens Healthineers Hit by Waning Covid-19 Test Sales
item.description: Siemens Healthineers profits fell sharply in the second quarter, with adjusted earnings at €681 million, as demand for its Covid-19 products declined, but it maintained its full-year outlook.

item.title: ABN AMRO Posts Solid Profit Beat
item.description: ABN AMRO posted above-forecast profits in the first quarter, helped by improved deposit margins from higher interest rates and lower impairments and raised its long-term target for return on equity.

item.title: Lonza Confirms Outlook
item.description: Lonza said it continues to expect a stronger second half of the year and reiterated its guidance for high single-digit sales and a core earnings margin of 30-31%.

item.title: E.ON Maintains Outlook as Profits Jump
item.description: E.ON reported higher adjusted earnings of €2.7 billion in the first quarter on increased sales and confirmed its profit guidance for the year.

item.description: Current Chief Executive Toni Petersson is set to become the oat-milk company’s co-chairman.
